g.id: connecting Health issues to Census Data
Issues include health issues, health access issues, and target groups. These are identified in the Scan of Community Health Assessments (CHAs)..
Each health assessment is associated with a hospital or clinic. They self-identify served municipalities.
339 municipalities of 351 are represented by the self-asssigned served communitiees in the CHAs.
We identify a suite of measurements from census data to associate with each municipality.
For each MUNICIPALITY, there is a group of ISSUES that can be identified with a suite of STATS.
For each ISSUE, the suite of STATS has many instances. Each measure therefore has an ensemble.
The ISSUES are connected via the DOCUMENTS that identify those issues. We generate a graph where the edges are weighted by the number of shared CHAs.
We create ISSUE groups by choosing thresholds and grouping rules. Different rule sets will create different groupings, some of which are mutually exclusive in ISSUES and some of which may not be.
Each ISSUE group is then identified with all the MUNICIPALITIES represented by all the ISSUES in the group. We therefore also have an ensemble of statistics for each measure.
